OL,3,CLib Dems call for 'like-minded' groups
OL,4,Cto work together post election
OL,6,FANALYSIS FROM POLITICAL REPORTER,
OL,7,FLEWIS WARNER
OL,9,FHarmer's intervention stops short of
OL,10,Fan explicit coalition pitch, but it is
OL,11,Fthe clearest public signal yet that
OL,12,Fparties are beginning to position
OL,13,Fthemselves for negotiations over who
OL,14,Fruns Birmingham City Council.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778523070
OL,3,CLib Dems call for 'like-minded' groups
OL,4,Cto work together post election
OL,6,FThe arithmetic alone underlines how
OL,7,Fdifficult any governing arrangement
OL,8,Fwill be. With 51 seats needed for a
OL,9,Fmajority, no single party or
OL,10,Fstraightforward pairing comes close,
OL,11,Fmeaning any administration would
OL,12,Flikely depend on a complex and
OL,13,Fpotentially unstable web of agreements
OL,14,Finvolving multiple parties and
OL,15,Findependents.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778523070
OL,3,CLib Dems call for 'like-minded' groups
OL,4,Cto work together post election
OL,6,FAlthough Reform UK emerged as the
OL,7,Flargest group, the fragmented chamber
OL,8,Fmeans influence is widely dispersed,
OL,9,Fand early manoeuvring is expected to
OL,10,Ffocus as much on smaller groups and
OL,11,Findependents as on the main parties.
OL,13,FThe Liberal Democrats do have recent
OL,14,Fexperience of coalition government in
OL,15,FBirmingham, having run the council
OL,16,Falongside the Conservatives between
OL,17,F2004 and 2012. But the current
OL,18,Fpolitical landscape is significantly
OL,19,Fmore fractured, making any comparable
OL,20,Farrangement harder to replicate.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778523070
OL,3,CLib Dems call for 'like-minded' groups
OL,4,Cto work together post election
OL,6,FWhile no party is yet openly framing
OL,7,Fdiscussions in terms of a formal
OL,8,Fcoalition, conversations are expected
OL,9,Fto continue behind the scenes over the
OL,10,Fweekend as councillors test where, if
OL,11,Fanywhere, workable agreements might
OL,12,Femerge.
OL,14,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,15,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,16,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,17,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,18,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,19,Fbelow...
